        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 11:15AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1114 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Taft, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Portland, Taft, Gregory, Bayside, and Taft Southwest.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 181 between mile markers 626 and 644.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 638 and 642.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
